<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12004b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12004b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12004b"> 4(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Abb&eacute; Mahe strikes menhir / Parle! Mais parle! / <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font>Erdeven<font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> / monolith</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">D&egrave;s 1825, <mark>l&apos;abb&eacute; Mah&eacute;</mark>, chanoine de Vannes, <mark>frappait</mark>, dit-on, dans un acc&egrave;s de fougue juv&eacute;nile sur <mark>un monolithe d&apos;Erdeven</mark>, et lui lan&ccedil;ait cette apostrophe virulente: &ldquo;<mark>Parle!</mark>&hellip; mais parle donc!&hellip;&rdquo; <br><font color="green">[It is said that in 1825, the abb&eacute; Mah&eacute;, canon of Vannes, overwhelmed with youthful ardour, struck a monolith in Erdeven and hurled at it this virulent apostrophe &ldquo;Speak!&hellip; but speak!&hellip;&rdquo;]</font> <small> l'Abb&eacute; A. Millon, <a name="AMPB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AMPB"><cite title="source">Pauvres Pierres! Les Megalithes Bretons devant la science</cite></a> (n.d) 7</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
